title: Abdullah Ibrahim interview, WOMAD July 1989
description: An interview I was lucky enough to have with the great South African pianist at WOMAD in Reading, England in 1989 - very moving memories of Johnny Dyani and discussion of the struggles of the exiled SA musicians during apartheid. A positive insight into Islam. Just wish I'd asked him about Thelonious Monk too...
